Kowloon's Jade Magistracy geological survey teams report that the Glasswash North Fan extraction sites are heavily haunted by ghosts of former extraction workers, victims of the Ashfall Monsoon that buried the work parties under a sulfur-laden ash fall. These extraction site haunts are actively hostile and have destroyed three survey instrument deployments. The Magistracy needs five killed to reduce ghost density enough for instrument placement teams to operate safely.
Five extraction site haunt kills are confirmed and Kowloon's Jade Magistracy survey teams have successfully deployed two instrument arrays in the North Fan zone. Preliminary mineral readings are already exceeding expectations. The extraction site haunts are not entirely suppressed — the Magistracy's documentation team notes they seem to be defending specific dig points rather than haunting randomly, which suggests the ghosts retain knowledge of the extraction survey data they were compiling when the Ashfall Monsoon killed them.
